summary:
The Council calls on the Government of Haiti to continue advancing security sector reform, including the development and implementation of the next five-year HNP Development Plan. The Council also underscores the need to strengthen Haitian judicial and correctional systems and welcomes efforts to create jobs and deliver basic social services.

The Council determines that the situation in Haiti continues to constitute a threat to international peace and security in the region and acts under Chapter VII of the UN Charter. It affirms the ownership and primary responsibility of the Government and people of Haiti over all aspects of the country's stabilization and welcomes steps taken by MINUSTAH to provide logistical and technical expertise to assist the Government.
The Security Council, 
Recalling its previous resolutions on Haiti, 
Decides to: 

Greater countrywide presence of State, promoting good governance; 
Recognize stability post-election crucial, calls on MINUSTAH to support; 
Welcomes MINUSTAH coordination with Haitian National Police; 
Encourages Haitian authorities to enhance HNP capacity; 
Prioritize 5-yr HNP Development Plan; 
Welcomes police training resumption; 
Condemns violence, rape; 
Urges accountability; 
Reaffirms MINUSTAH human rights mandate; 
Welcomes MINUSTAHâ€™s work; 
Requests MINUSTAH community violence reduction.
The Security Council:



22. Emphasizes the need for regular updates to MINUSTAH's planning documents, such as the concept of operations and rules of engagement, in line with relevant resolutions, and requests the Secretary-General to report on them to the Council and troop- and police-contributing countries;

23. Requests the Secretary-General to report semi-annually on MINUSTAH's mandate implementation, no later than 45 days prior to its expiration;

24. Asks the Secretary-General to include in his reports a comprehensive assessment of security threats in Haiti, focusing on the protective environment for all, particularly women and children, and progress in sustainable resettlement of displaced persons, and to propose options to reconfigure MINUSTAH's composition as needed;

25. Decides to remain seized of the matter.
